transcription.text:
Speaker 1: This is Charles.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: I had ordered four blue, then I was automatically, a month later, I was automatically sent another—

Speaker 2: Prescription, and I don't want, I don't want it resent every month.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Michael Malin?

Speaker 1: Yep.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: It looks like you're a VIP member here, Michael.

Speaker 1: We completely get it.

Speaker 2: If you don't necessarily need the pills every single month, we won't hold you to it.

Speaker 1: If you'd like, so you can have some time to use what you have, I can pause everything—

Speaker 2: For the next five months.

Speaker 1: We won't charge you or send you anything.

Speaker 2: And then if you need them earlier, just give us a call, okay?

Speaker 1: I don't want it ever.

Speaker 2: I don't want to pause it, you know, for good, please.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Were you not a fan of the pills?

Speaker 1: No, they're fine, but I want some more all over.

Speaker 2: I don't want them automatically sent to me.

Speaker 1: Gotcha.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So for the prescription, to keep it alive, that's the most important thing, to keep the—

Speaker 2: Prescription alive for the Viagra.

Speaker 1: So if you'd like, we can go all the way up to half a year.

Speaker 2: That way you have the prescription alive and be able to order it whenever you want.

Speaker 1: It wouldn't come monthly.

Speaker 2: It'd be like once or twice a year.

Speaker 1: That's the best that we can do to keep the prescription alive.

Speaker 2: No, I don't want to keep them alive.

Speaker 1: Why don't you want to keep it alive?

Speaker 2: I just don't.

Speaker 1: I don't want to be responsible for that every so often.

Speaker 2: I can...

Speaker 1: Once a year?

Speaker 2: Well, I'm fine.

Speaker 1: I don't want it.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: What are you going to do when you run out?

Speaker 2: Oh, fine.

Speaker 1: I'll order again.

Speaker 2: If they won't take my order, I won't order it.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Good luck in the future.

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: Take care.

Speaker 2: How do I know this is canceled?

Speaker 1: You can go online and see it.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: You'll send me an email?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Take care.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
